<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="313" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[881,939,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">ventr</emphasis>
- and 
<emphasis box="[1009,1104,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">dentatus</emphasis>
referring to the ventroapical denticle of the valva.
</paragraph>
